title: Ball State soccer takes close MAC win
text:
Ball State soccer takes close MAC win The Star Press 10:06 p.m. EDT October 4, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
SOCCER 
Ball State improved its record to 4-0 in the Mid-American Conference with a 2-1 win over Central Michigan. Chelsy Swackhamer and Leah Mattingly scored the Ball State goals, with Mattingly’s coming late in the second half to seal the win. 
WOMEN’S FIELD HOCKEY 
Ball State dropped a close 3-2 match to Virgina Commonwealth. Lexi Kavanaugh scored the initial goal for Ball State off a deflected penalty corner shot by Bryce Barnes . Bethany Han also added a goal, her second in two games. Jordan Dues recorded five saves in goal for the Cardinals. Read or Share this story: http://tspne.ws/1Rq0kS7 TOP VIDEOS
